<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="23" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="23">
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. porphyromelaena" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="porphyromelaena">P. porphyromelaena</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. sabahana" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sabahana">P. sabahana</taxonomicName>
, to which it is closely related in the phylogenetic tree (Fig. 1), but differs in the presence of xanthones and the absence of argopsin and norargopsin. 
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="23">Kistenich et al. (in press)</bibRefCitation>
showed that probably all Neotropical records of this species (e.g., by 
<bibRefCitation author="Timdal, E" journalOrPublisher="The Lichenologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="337 - 362" title="Studies on Phyllopsora (Ramalinaceae) in Peru." url="https://doi.org/10.1017/S0024282908007846" volume="40" year="2008 b">Timdal 2008b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Timdal, E" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Lichenologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" pagination="319 - 351" title="The lichen genus Phyllopsora (Ramalinaceae) in the West Indies." volume="106" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
) belong in another species, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. neotinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="neotinica">P. neotinica</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Phyllopsora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Phyllopsora chodatinica" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="23" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chodatinica">Phyllopsora chodatinica</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 3B) is new to Malaysia, New Caledonia, and Vanuatu.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
